President Cyril Ramaphosa says there's still an opportunity to deliver infrastructure. JOHANNESBURG - Mounting job losses have not altogether dampened President Cyril Ramaphosa's spirits. In his weekly newsletter 'From the desk of the President', Ramaphosa remains optimistic the country will be able to cushion the blow of the COVID-19 pandemic. READ: President Ramaphosa defends COVID-19 regulations Writing ahead of Tuesday's inaugural infrastructural symposium -- where billions of rand worth of projects will be discussed -- Ramaphosa says there's still an opportunity to deliver infrastructure. He is looking at areas as such as water, transportation, energy, digital, human settlements and agriculture. READ: Emergency budget to be tabled on 24 June At the symposium, the president and other roleplayers are expected to detail information on sponsorships. The symposium takes place a day before Finance Minister Tito Mboweni is scheduled to table a revised national budget in Parliament. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.